## SECTION 4 — Data Access Rules

### Always use the real Supabase client
```ts
// ✅
import { supabase } from '@/lib/supabase'
const { data } = await supabase.from('events').select('*')

// ❌ Never in production
import { MOCK_EVENTS } from '@devcon-plus/supabase'
```

### Point balance field names
```ts
// ✅ Correct field names (as of DB migration)
profile.spendable_points   // current redeemable balance — decremented on redemption
profile.lifetime_points    // total ever earned — never decremented — used for tier tracking

// ❌ Does not exist in live DB
profile.total_points
```

### Forms — always React Hook Form + Zod
```tsx
// ✅
const { register, handleSubmit, formState: { errors } } = useForm<FormData>({
  resolver: zodResolver(formSchema)
})

// ❌ Never
const [value, setValue] = useState('')
<input value={value} onChange={e => setValue(e.target.value)} />
```

### Pre-fill registration forms
```tsx
// Always pre-populate from the authenticated user's profile
const { user } = useAuthStore()
const defaultValues = {
  full_name: user?.full_name ?? '',
  email: user?.email ?? '',
  school_or_company: user?.school_or_company ?? '',
}
```

